    "Other possible applications of VR in surgical orthopedic surgery training include arthroplasty, fracture fixation, intramedullary nail and pedicle screw implantation [104].",
    "When compared to conventional learning techniques in orthopedic education, immersive virtual reality has been found to be more effective in mediating non-technical and technical skills [105].",
    "Generative AI has the ability to transform virtual assistants from static information sources to dynamic learning companions.",
    "The employment of 3D visualization and generative AI assistance in VR can improve learning by creating a more dynamic and realistic environment for examining structures than traditional techniques [106].",
    "Moreover, orthopedic residents might benefit from an AI-powered virtual assistant that can answer complicated queries and guide procedures in VR, potentially acting as a valuable training tool."
